The information wouldn't be lost to the general populace. It would just be seldom known and ignored. The average person today knows a bit about Pluto, but won't be able to tell you anything about Ceres, Eris, Sedna, Haumea, or any of the other dwarf planets. They wouldn't even be able to tell you that the Dawn probe is orbiting Ceres right now. This isn't because the average person is dumb or anything, it's just that these things are off their radar.

The idea is that Pluto would just become another tiny space thing that the average person doesn't know or care about. People that are actively interested in space will still know about it, but they won't have the general public behind them.





